---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---

<BaseLayout
  title="About the author"
  description="About Feliks Mamczur, author of Prompted Psyche, a publication and expert platform on AI, cyberpsychology and Human-AI Interaction."
>
  <article class="lovable-page about-page">
    <header class="lovable-page-hero">
      <div class="lovable-container">
        <div class="lovable-heading-narrow">
          <p class="eyebrow">Author</p>
          <h1>About the author</h1>
          <p class="lede">
            My name is Feliks Mamczur. I write about the human side of AI: how
            language models and generative systems affect cognition, attention, trust,
            communication, creativity and work.
          </p>
          <p class="hero-subnote">
            I develop Prompted Psyche as an independent publication and expert platform
            at the intersection of AI, cognitive psychology, cyberpsychology and
            Human-AI Interaction.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </header>

    <section class="editorial-block">
      <div class="lovable-container editorial-split">
        <div>
          <p class="eyebrow">01</p>
          <p class="meta-kicker">Human side</p>
        </div>
        <div>
          <h2>Why I write about AI</h2>
          <div class="editorial-copy">
            <p>
              AI is usually discussed as a tool, a market force or a technical
              infrastructure. I am interested in another layer: what happens to people
              when AI enters thinking, writing, decision-making, emotion and
              communication.
            </p>
            <p>
              Prompted Psyche is where I organize that perspective through essays,
              notes and concepts. The project asks how people trust AI, how they
              delegate judgment, how conversational systems shape emotion and how
              generative tools reorganize creative and professional work.
            </p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="editorial-block">
      <div class="lovable-container editorial-split">
        <div>
          <p class="eyebrow">02</p>
          <p class="meta-kicker">Perspective</p>
        </div>
        <div>
          <h2>My perspective</h2>
          <div class="editorial-copy">
            <p>
              I bring together several fields of interest: cognitive psychology,
              cyberpsychology, Human-AI Interaction, communication and creative
              practice. I do not present this as an institutional research program or
              a formal academic title. It is an authorial, source-informed perspective
              on how AI enters human thought, emotion, language and work.
            </p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="editorial-block with-side-note">
      <div class="lovable-container editorial-split">
        <div>
          <p class="eyebrow">03</p>
          <p class="meta-kicker">Interpretive lens</p>
        </div>
        <div>
          <h2>Where film comes in</h2>
          <div class="editorial-copy">
            <p>
              My background in film, editing and post-production shapes how I think
              about AI: through narrative, attention, image, emotion and the way
              technologies reorganize creative and communicative work.
            </p>
            <p>
              That experience helps me notice how interfaces guide attention, how
              systems shape rhythm and how technologies change what people create,
              believe and pass on to others.
            </p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
      <aside class="floating-note" aria-hidden="true">
        <span></span>
        Narrative, attention, image, emotion
      </aside>
    </section>

    <section class="lovable-section" aria-labelledby="read-title">
      <div class="lovable-container">
        <div class="compact-heading">
          <p class="eyebrow">04</p>
          <h2 id="read-title">What to read here</h2>
        </div>

        <div class="lovable-lens-grid">
          <article class="lens-item">
            <p>Articles</p>
            <h3>Long-form essays</h3>
            <span>
              Developed arguments on AI, cyberpsychology, Human-AI Interaction,
              trust, attention, work and culture.
            </span>
          </article>
          <article class="lens-item lens-item-offset">
            <p>Notes</p>
            <h3>Shorter observations</h3>
            <span>
              Compact reflections, working ideas and signals from the changing
              relationship between people and AI systems.
            </span>
          </article>
          <article class="lens-item">
            <p>Concepts</p>
            <h3>A shared vocabulary</h3>
            <span>
              Terms that help name what happens when AI enters cognition,
              communication, decision-making and creative practice.
            </span>
          </article>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="editorial-block">
      <div class="lovable-container editorial-split">
        <div>
          <p class="eyebrow">05</p>
          <p class="meta-kicker">Consulting</p>
        </div>
        <div>
          <h2>Consulting as an extension of the work</h2>
          <div class="editorial-copy">
            <p>
              Consulting, workshops and talks grow from the same perspective. I help
              organizations think more clearly about AI literacy, Human-AI
              Interaction, trust, decision-making and the psychology of working with
              generative tools.
            </p>
            <p>
              The consulting page explains the formats and the kinds of questions I
              can help with.
            </p>
            <p>
              <a class="text-link" href="/consulting/">See consulting</a>
            </p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="lovable-final-links">
      <div class="lovable-container final-link-grid">
        <a href="/articles/">Read articles</a>
        <a href="/concepts/">Explore concepts</a>
      </div>
    </section>
  </article>
</BaseLayout>
